e` from URL params via `useParams()`\n   355→  - Stores `{ code, capturedAt }` as JSON in `localStorage` key `referral_code`\n   356→  - Gracefully handles localStorage unavailability (private browsing, storage full)\n   357→  - Returns `<Navigate to=\"/\" replace />` for immediate redirect\n   358→- Added `<Route path=\"/r/:code\" element={<ReferralCapture />} />` before the catch-all `*` route\n   359→**Verification**: `pnpm lint` passed (18/18). Platform typecheck passed. Pre-existing backend typecheck error (HealthDeps) — not introduced by this change.\n   360→\n   361→## Iteration 19 — 2026-03-25T12:58:52Z — OK\n   362→- **Log**: iteration-019.log\n   363→\n   364→## Iteration 20 — 2026-03-25 — OK\n   365→\n   366→**Item**: [frontend] `useReferralApply` hook — auto-apply stored referral code on authentication\n   367→**Status**: Done\n   368→**Changes**:\n   369→- Created `apps/platform/src/features/referral/hooks/useReferralApply.ts`:\n   370→  - Watches `isAuthenticated`, `accessToken`, `address` from session/wallet hooks\n   371→  - Reads `referral_code` from localStorage (set by `/r/:code` ReferralCapture)\n   372→  - Calls `applyReferralCode(token, code)` on authentication\n   373→  - Clears localStorage on success or permanent failure (ALREADY_LINKED, SELF_REFERRAL, NOT_FOUND, INVALID)\n   374→  - Keeps localStorage on transient failure (network error, 500) for retry on next auth\n   375→  - Uses `appliedRef` to prevent duplicate calls within same auth session\n   376→  - Handles corrupt/missing localStorage data gracefully\n   377→- Created `apps/platform/src/features/referral/index.ts` barrel export\n   378→- Updated `App.tsx`: imported `useReferralApply`, called in `AppContent` (inside auth provider tree)\n   379→**Verification**: `pnpm lint` passed (18/18, 0 errors). Platform typecheck passed. Pre-existing backend typecheck error (HealthDeps) — not introduced by this change.\n   380→\n   381→## Iteration 20 — 2026-03-25T13:06:04Z — OK\n   382→- **Log*