{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01Y23uHuJLb188RP28MGNAiH","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect. I have the complete referral pattern. Here's the summary of the existing referral architecture:\n\n## Referral Patterns Summary\n\n### API Layer (`referral-api.ts`)\n- **Backend URL**: `VITE_FAIRNESS_BACKEND_URL` env var (default `http://127.0.0.1:3100`)\n- **Auth**: JWT Bearer token from `useSession().accessToken` \n- **Core endpoints**:\n  - `POST /referral/code` — Set/replace player's referral code\n  - `GET /referral/code` — Fetch player's current referral code\n  - `POST /referral/apply` — Apply a referral code (link to referrer)\n  - `GET /referral/stats` — Summary stats (referred count, active count, volumes, earnings)\n  - `GET /referral/earnings` — Paginated per-game earnings log\n  - `POST /referral/claim` — Request async claim of pending earnings\n  - `GET /referral/claim/{claimId}` — Poll claim status\n\n### Key Response Types\n- **ReferralCodeResponse**: `{ code, url }`\n- **ApplyReferralResponse**: `{ referrer, benefit }`\n- **ReferralStatsResponse**: Aggregated earning metrics (`referredCount`, `activeCount`, `totalVolumeLamports`, `totalEarnedLamports`, `totalRebateLamports`, `pendingLamports`)\n- **ReferralEarningItem**: Per-game earning record (`roundId`, `gameType`, `refereeWallet`, `wagerLamports`, `earnedLamports`, `createdAt`)\n- **ClaimResponse**: Claim tracking (`claimId`, `amountLamports`, `status: \"pending\" | \"completed\" | \"failed\"`, optional `txSignature`)\n\n### Hooks & Auto-Apply\n- **useReferralApply()**: Auto-applies referral code from localStorage (set via `/r/:code` route) on first auth. Clears on success or permanent failure; retries on transient failures.\n- Stores code in `localStorage.referral_code` as JSON\n\n### ReferralPage Structure\n- Responsive layout with four main sections:\n  1. **ReferralLinkCard** — Display/copy referral link + code\n  2. **ReferralStatsCard** — Summary metrics (referred count, earnings, rebates)\n  3. **ReferralClaimCard** — Pending earnings & claim button (async with polling)\n  4. **ReferralEarningsTable** — Paginated per-game earning history\n\n### Integration Points for Profile Settings\nFor a profile settings referral section, you would:\n1. Use `getReferralCode(token)` to fetch current code\n2. Use `getReferralStats(token)` for dashboard overview\n3. Use `setReferralCode(token, code)` if you want to regenerate (optional)\n4. Display these in a compact card/section — likely read-only in settings (full editing in dedicated `/referral` page)\n\nThe pattern is **simple**: session context provides token, call API, display/update state. No complex polling needed for settings view — just fetch on mount and cache locally."},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: a8892f52dfa59044e (use SendMessage with to: 'a8892f52dfa59044e' to continue this agent)\n<usage>total_tokens: 40331\ntool_uses: 4\nduration_ms: 13229</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"eb5de170-2e49-4887-a19e-0983dec4d654","uuid":"f582d9c1-4526-4e34-82c2-361cd63fcdc1","timestamp":"2026-03-25T13:38:24.061Z","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Read these files fully and report their contents:\n1. `sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/src/lib/referral-api.ts` - the API client\n2. `sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/src/features/referral/hooks/useReferralApply.ts` - the apply hook\n3. `sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/src/features/referral/index.ts` - barrel exports\n4. `sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/src/features/referral/ReferralPage.tsx` - the referral page\n\nI need to understand the existing referral patterns to build a profile settings section that integrates with them.","agentId":"a8892f52dfa59044e","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect. I have the complete referral pattern. Here's the summary of the existing referral architecture:\n\n## Referral Patterns Summary\n\n### API Layer (`referral-api.ts`)\n- **Backend URL**: `VITE_FAIRNESS_BACKEND_URL` env var (default `http://127.0.0.1:3100`)\n- **Auth**: JWT Bearer token from `useSession().accessToken` \n- **Core endpoints**:\n  - `POST /referral/code` — Set/replace player's referral code\n  - `GET /referral/code` — Fetch player's current referral code\n  - `POST /referral/apply` — Apply a referral code (link to referrer)\n  - `GET /referral/stats` — Summary stats (referred count, active count, volumes, earnings)\n  - `GET /referral/earnings` — Paginated per-game earnings log\n  - `POST /referral/claim` — Request async claim of pending earnings\n  - `GET /referral/claim/{claimId}` — Poll claim status\n\n### Key Response Types\n- **ReferralCodeResponse**: `{ code, url }`\n- **ApplyReferralResponse**: `{ referrer, benefit }`\n- **ReferralStatsResponse**: Aggregated earning metrics (`referredCount`, `activeCount`, `totalVolumeLamports`, `totalEarnedLamports`, `totalRebateLamports`, `pendingLamports`)\n- **ReferralEarningItem**: Per-game earning record (`roundId`, `gameType`, `refereeWallet`, `wagerLamports`, `earnedLamports`, `createdAt`)\n- **ClaimResponse**: Claim tracking (`claimId`, `amountLamports`, `status: \"pending\" | \"completed\" | \"failed\"`, optional `txSignature`)\n\n### Hooks & Auto-Apply\n- **useReferralApply()**: Auto-applies referral code from localStorage (set via `/r/:code` route) on first auth. Clears on success or permanent failure; retries on transient failures.\n- Stores code in `localStorage.referral_code` as JSON\n\n### ReferralPage Structure\n- Responsive layout with four main sections:\n  1. **ReferralLinkCard** — Display/copy referral link + code\n  2. **ReferralStatsCard** — Summary metrics (referred count, earnings, rebates)\n  3. **ReferralClaimCard** — Pending earnings & claim button (async with polling)\n  4. **ReferralEarningsTable** — Paginated per-game earning history\n\n### Integration Points for Profile Settings\nFor a profile settings referral section, you would:\n1. Use `getReferralCode(token)` to fetch current code\n2. Use `getReferralStats(token)` for dashboard overview\n3. Use `setReferralCode(token, code)` if you want to regenerate (optional)\n4. Display these in a compact card/section — likely read-only in settings (full editing in dedicated `/referral` page)\n\nThe pattern is **simple**: session context provides token, call API, display/update state. No complex polling needed for settings view — just fetch on mount and cache locally."}],"totalDurationMs":13229,"totalTokens":40331,"totalToolUseCount":4,"usage":{"input_tokens":1693,"cache_creation_input_tokens":7743,"cache_read_input_tokens":30132,"output_tokens":763,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":7743},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}}}
